76561198058246566,Recommended,287070,30678214,Posted: 22 March,all,writerrhino,"Battle Academy is a fun turn-based tabletop tactics game that reminds me of my old hex-map, counters and dice days, except BA does all the die rolls and result table look-ups for you. Don't expect sprawling maps or dazzling graphics, this is a minimalist game, but it's great for a few minutes of fun at the end of a long day when you have neither the time or the brain cells for an evening-long gaming slog. I got mine on sale and think I got a good gaming value for the money. If you're intruiged by WWII armor combat and your gaming time is limited, I would recommend it."
